Zomato Data Worldwide — Power BI Dashboard
An interactive Power BI dashboard analyzing global restaurant data from Zomato across multiple countries and continents. This project highlights key business metrics, geographic trends, cuisine diversity, and customer experience indicators using rich visualizations and data modeling techniques.

Project Overview:
This project explores Zomato’s worldwide restaurant dataset to uncover insights about restaurant distribution, cuisine availability, cost patterns, and service offerings such as online delivery and table booking.

The dashboard includes:

9,551 restaurants

146 cuisine types

1.20K average cost

2.67 average rating

Restaurant distribution by country, city, and continent

Cuisine frequency and diversity analysis

Average cost comparison across top restaurant names

Online delivery availability (74% Yes, 26% No)


Tools & Techniques

Power BI Desktop

Power Query for data cleaning and transformation

DAX for KPI calculations and measures

Geospatial mapping for country‑level restaurant distribution

Interactive slicers for continent, country, cuisine, and rating filters

Data modeling to support relationships and drill‑down analysis


Key Insights

India, Singapore, and Indonesia show the highest restaurant density.

North Indian, Chinese, and Café cuisines appear most frequently across regions.

Online delivery is widely available, with over 7K restaurants offering the service.

Average cost varies significantly across top restaurant names, with some exceeding 0.8M in local currency.

Cities like New Delhi, Gurgaon, and Noida dominate restaurant counts within the dataset.

Table booking availability (88% Yes, 12% No)
